          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1596539359949-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are almost cooked, slice the <strong>brioche buns </strong>in half</p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to a baking tray, cut side up, and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p><p>Return the <strong>drained peas</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, remove from the heat and stir in the <strong>wasabi paste</strong></p><p>Mash the peas roughly with a potato masher until lightly crushed – these are your <strong>wasabi peas</strong></p>",
